cs.GT, cs.AI, cs.DS, cs.DM, cs.CC 

The paper deals with game theory and algorithms for computing Nash equilibria, which are topics commonly found in the cs.GT (Game Theory) sub-category. The paper also discusses computational challenges and provides a polynomial-time algorithm, which suggests that it could also belong to the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-category. The use of binary trees and combinatorial bargaining suggests that it could also belong to the cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) sub-categories. Finally, the paper discusses fairness and social welfare, which could place it in the cs.CC (Computational Complexity) sub-category.
